  Texas COVID-19 Vaccine Tracker





  The reach of COVID-19 on Texas and the world has been devastating. As our state joins a global effort to put coronavirus into our past, we are tracking the Texas vaccine roll-out as it unfolds in real-time.
  Texas has 22,421,178 people above the age of 16 who at some point will be eligible for a vaccine. As of Mar 23, 2021, the state has:


   | Fully Vaccinated: 3,237,521 people or 14% of the population 16+  | Vaccinated w/ At Least One Dose: 6,406,693 people or 29% of the population 16+  | Administered: 47,345 doses in one day on Mar 23, 2021 or 0.21% of the population 16+  | A 7-Day Average of 126,518 administered per day or 0.56% of the population 16+



